          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1661184265314-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Drain your <strong>mozzarella</strong>, then pat and squeeze as much liquid out as you can with kitchen paper</p><p>Tear the <strong>drained mozzarella </strong>into rough, bite-sized pieces</p><p>Wash your <strong>spinach</strong>, then pat dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Once the<strong> </strong>bean stew<strong> </strong>has thickened slightly, stir the <strong>spinach</strong> through and cook with a lid on, for 2-3 min further or until the spinach has wilted – this is your <strong>Italian bean stew</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1661184272736-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
